## STEP 8 — Pass user's Bank Records deposits into the chat

The chat's attachment picker lets users share their own FD cards.
These should come from the user's existing Bank Records data in Supabase.

In the Groups section component, fetch the user's deposits:
```tsx
const [userBankDeposits, setUserBankDeposits] = useState([])

useEffect(() => {
  if (!user?.id) return
  supabase
    .from('bank_records')
    .select('data')
    .eq('user_id', user.id)
    .single()
    .then(({ data }) => {
      if (data?.data?.deposits) {
        setUserBankDeposits(data.data.deposits)
      }
    })
}, [user?.id])
```

Then pass `userDeposits={userBankDeposits}` to `<GroupFinanceChat />`.

This means FDs shared in the chat are always live from the user's
actual Bank Records — not hardcoded sample data.

