## STEP 10 — Document upload (optional enhancement)

The doc attachment currently simulates an upload. To wire real file
uploads via Supabase Storage:

1. Create a storage bucket called `group-documents` in Supabase dashboard
   with these settings:
   - Public: false
   - File size limit: 10MB
   - Allowed MIME types: `application/pdf, image/*, application/vnd.ms-excel,
     application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet`

2. In the `AttachPicker` component's doc tab, replace the simulated
   upload with:
```tsx
async function handleFileUpload(file: File) {
  const path = `${groupId}/${Date.now()}_${file.name}`
  const { data, error } = await supabase.storage
    .from('group-documents')
    .upload(path, file)

  if (!error && data) {
    const { data: urlData } = supabase.storage
      .from('group-documents')
      .getPublicUrl(data.path)

    onAttach('doc', {
      name: file.name,
      size: `${Math.round(file.size / 1024)} KB`,
      type: file.name.split('.').pop()?.toUpperCase() || 'FILE',
      url:  urlData.publicUrl,
    })
  }
}
```

3. Wire the `DocCard` component's download button to open `doc.url` when present:
```tsx
onClick={() => doc.url && window.open(doc.url, '_blank')}
```

